Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
A long time ago (about 3 years) i've coded an ANSI-Viewer for CLI-Usage in
100% ASM-Code...I use this tool since the first time, but it had some dis-
advantages i don't like very much...so I decided to fix all these nasty bugs
to re-release it, but this time bugfixed...:)

What it is
~~~~~~~~~~
A simple, but very fast animation viewer for ANSI'S & ASCII'S. It displays
all textfiles on an own screen (naturally it's 640x256 PAL Screen, but you
could promote it to your needs!) with an ANSI-Colortable, meaning you see
all pictures like an user in your BBS could saw them!

What it needs
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Kickstart V37 or better (Kick 1.3 suxx!)
asl.library V36 or better (for the FileRequester)
Some Files to view...:)

How it works
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Simple...start it direct from CLI, and BBS-View pops up a Filerequester and
asks you for a filename...select NOPE!/ABORT to cancel operation, or double-
click on a filename to view it.

Of course you could give a filename to view it immediatly, for more infos
enter 'BBS-VIEW ?' in CLI-Prompt.

After displaying the Textfile, BBS-View waits for a left-Mouseclick to exit.

If you view animations and don't want to see the whole anim, simply press
the Closegadget to abort displaying.

